THE Scottish independence referendum has placed a special emphasis on young voters, as 16 and 17-year-olds will go to the polls for the first time Video report: Young campaigners have their say THE Scottish independence referendum has placed a special emphasis on young voters, as 16 and 17-year-olds will go to the polls for the first time. 

The Scotsman met two young campaigners as they laid out their hopes for Scotland’s future.
